name: Yopaxtul
content:
A Vratix from the planet Thyferra, Yopaxtul was an athlete who was active during the last years of the Galactic Republic. In 22 BBY, Yopaxtul participated in the prestigious Mobquet Presents: Fastest Land Beings racing meet on Teyr, winning the one hundred meter hexaped race, setting a new speed record of 6.132 seconds in the process.
Originally from the planet Thyferra in the Polith system, Yopaxtul was a member of the six-limbed, insectoid Vratix species and a sprinter active during the last years of the Galactic Republic. In 22 BBY, Yopaxtul competed in the prestigious Mobquet Presents: Fastest Land Beings racing meet, held annually in the city of Pyre Folas on the planet Teyr. The Vratix won the meet's one hundred meter hexaped race, setting a new speed record of 6.132 seconds in the process. For the Vratix's victory, Yopaxtul was awarded a medal, and later posed in a picture along with the meets' biped and quadruped race winnersâ€”the Teek Yeep and the Selonian Pumav, respectfully. The event of that year's Mobquet Presents, along with Yopaxtul's participated, were reported on by the HoloNet News.
